"n.蔓藤图饰 【记】 arab(阿拉伯)+esque →有阿拉伯风格的图案 n. 阿拉伯式图饰(一种复杂的装饰性的设计, 由花、叶及几何图案缠绕在一起, 又叫蔓藤花纹) 【记】arab阿拉伯, que缺－阿拉伯特别缺水. 所以他们用蔓藤图饰来求雨－阿拉伯式图饰. 【记】源自arab 阿拉伯，音：阿拉伯壁刻，阿拉伯壁刻图案 arabesque (n.)  1610s, ""Moorish or Arabic ornamental design,"" from French arabesque (16c.), from Italian arabesco, from Arabo ""Arab,"" with reference to Moorish architecture. As a ballet pose, first attested 1830. Musical sense, in reference to an ornamented theme, is from 1864, originally the title given by Robert Schumann to one of his piano pieces."
